tudies, feminism, critical race theory, and law and economics. Others address substantive areas, including environmental, criminal, contract, torts, and family law, as well as professional responsibility. Together the essays introduce a new school of legal thought that will make a signal contribution to contemporary discussions of law.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aChristianity and law. 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh1 aAllegretti, Joseph G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlschuler, Albert W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBainbridge, Stephen M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerman, Harold J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBradley, Gerard V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarmella, Angela C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarmella, Angela C., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCarter, Stephen L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarter, W. Burlette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaudill, David S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCochran, Robert F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCochran, Robert, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCollett, Teresa Stanton, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDouglas, Davison M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuncan, Richard F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFailinger, Marie A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarvey, George E.